<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3152] MockDirectoryWrapper should wrap the lockfactory</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3152</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;After applying the patch from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3147&quot; title=&quot;MockDirectoryWrapper should track open file handles of IndexOutput too&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LUCENE-3147&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;, I added a line to make the test fail if it cannot remove its temporary directory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I ran &apos;ant test&apos; on linux 50 times, and it passed all 50 times.&lt;br/&gt;
But on windows, it failed often because of write.lock... this is because of unclosed writers in the test.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;MockDirectoryWrapper is currently unaware of this write.lock, I think it should wrap the lockfactory so that .close() will fail if there are any outstanding locks.&lt;br/&gt;
Then hopefully these tests would fail on linux too.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
